        output='Based on the provided prospectus excerpts, here is the breakdown of how the mergers were executed, the accounting methodology applied, and the limitations regarding standalone financial statements:\n\n### 1. How xAI and X Holdings Were Merged\nThe mergers were executed in two primary steps, both effected through **share exchanges**:\n*   **The X Merger (March 28, 2025):** xAI acquired X Holdings Corp. (“X”) and X.AI Corp., making them wholly-owned subsidiaries of xAI. \n    *   *Exchange Mechanics:* X Common Stock converted into xAI Common Stock at a ratio of 2.776-to-1. X.AI Corp. common and preferred stock converted 1-to-1 into xAI Common Stock and xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock, respectively.\n*   **The xAI Merger (February 2, 2026):** SpaceX acquired xAI, making it a wholly-owned subsidiary of SpaceX.\n    *   *Exchange Mechanics:* xAI Common Stock and customer warrants converted into SpaceX Common Stock at a fixed exchange ratio of 0.1433 (on a pre-split basis). xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock converted into SpaceX Common Stock (though eligible service providers had the option to elect cash at $75.46 per share). \n*   **2026 Stock Split:** On May 4, 2026, SpaceX executed a 5-for-1 forward stock split. All historical share and per-share information was retroactively adjusted to reflect this split.\n\n### 2. Accounting Basis and Retrospective Recast Methodology\nBecause Elon Musk held a controlling financial interest (majority voting interest) in SpaceX, xAI, and X during all presented periods, the transactions were accounted for as **reorganizations of entities under common control**. This resulted in a "change in reporting entity" with the following accounting treatments:\n*   **Retrospective Combination:** The consolidated financial statements were retrospectively recast to combine the net assets of SpaceX, xAI, and X at their **historical carrying amounts** for all periods presented.\n*   **No Goodwill:** No new goodwill or intangible assets were recorded as a result of the mergers.\n*   **Eliminations:** All historical intercompany balances and related-party transactions between the entities were eliminated in consolidation.\n*   **Equity Adjustments:** Historical shareholders\' equity reflects a continuation of SpaceX\'s historical equity combined with X and xAI\'s equity, adjusted by the respective merger exchange ratios.\n*   **Preferred Stock Exception:** Unlike the common stock, xAI’s Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock was **not** retrospectively recast on an as-converted basis. Because it represented a separate equity class of a legally distinct predecessor entity, it is presented in its historical legal form for prior periods, and its conversion to SpaceX Common Stock is only recognized prospectively in the period the merger actually closed (Q1 2026).\n\n### 3. Limitations on Separating Standalone SpaceX Financials\n*   **Omission of Separate Statements:** The prospectus explicitly states that because the consolidated financial statements already reflect the retrospective combination of the entities under common control for all periods presented, **separate financial statements for xAI and X are not provided.**\n*   **Inability to Isolate Legacy SpaceX:** Due to the retrospective recasting and the elimination of all historical intercompany/related-party transactions, the financial data presented represents the combined enterprise as a single reporting entity. Consequently, the provided documents do not contain the isolated, standalone historical financials for the legacy SpaceX aerospace and Starlink businesses separate from the X and xAI operations.',
